{"content":"---\ntitle: \"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext Method\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\napi_name: \n  - \"ICorDebugProcess.SetThreadContext\"\napi_location: \n  - \"mscordbi.dll\"\napi_type: \n  - \"COM\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext method [.NET Framework debugging]\"\n  - \"SetThreadContext method, ICorDebugProcess interface [.NET Framework debugging]\"\nms.assetid: a7b50175-2bf1-40be-8f65-64aec7aa1247\ntopic_type: \n  - \"apiref\"\nauthor: \"rpetrusha\"\nms.author: \"ronpet\"\n---\n# ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext Method\nSets the context for the given thread in this process.  \n  \n## Syntax  \n  \n```  \nHRESULT SetThreadContext(  \n    [in] DWORD threadID,  \n    [in] ULONG32 contextSize,  \n    [in, length_is(contextSize), size_is(contextSize)]  \n    BYTE context[]);  \n```  \n  \n## Parameters  \n `threadID`  \n [in] The ID of the thread for which to set the context.  \n  \n `contextSize`  \n [in] The size of the `context` array.  \n  \n `context`  \n [in] An array of bytes that describe the thread's context.  \n  \n The context specifies the architecture of the processor on which the thread is executing.  \n  \n## Remarks  \n The debugger should call this method rather than the Win32 `SetThreadContext` function, because the thread may actually be in a \"hijacked\" state, in which its context has been temporarily changed. This method should be used only when a thread is in native code. Use [ICorDebugRegisterSet](../../../../docs/framework/unmanaged-api/debugging/icordebugregisterset-interface.md) for threads in managed code. You should never need to modify the context of a thread during an out-of-band (OOB) debug event.  \n  \n The data passed must be a context structure for the current platform.  \n  \n This method can corrupt the runtime if used improperly.  \n  \n## Requirements  \n **Platforms:** See [System Requirements](../../../../docs/framework/get-started/system-requirements.md).  \n  \n **Header:** CorDebug.idl, CorDebug.h  \n  \n **Library:** CorGuids.lib  \n  \n **.NET Framework Versions:** [!INCLUDE[net_current_v20plus](../../../../includes/net-current-v20plus-md.md)]\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,534],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext Method\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\napi_name: \n  - \"ICorDebugProcess.SetThreadContext\"\napi_location: \n  - \"mscordbi.dll\"\napi_type: \n  - \"COM\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext method [.NET Framework debugging]\"\n  - \"SetThreadContext method, ICorDebugProcess interface [.NET Framework debugging]\"\nms.assetid: a7b50175-2bf1-40be-8f65-64aec7aa1247\ntopic_type: \n  - \"apiref\"\nauthor: \"rpetrusha\"\nms.author: \"ronpet\"","nodes":[{"content":"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext Method","nodes":[{"pos":[0,41],"content":"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext Method","nodes":[{"content":"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext Method","pos":[0,41]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[541,582],"content":"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext Method","linkify":"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext Method","nodes":[{"content":"ICorDebugProcess::SetThreadContext Method","pos":[0,41]}]},{"content":"Sets the context for the given thread in this process.","pos":[583,637]},{"pos":[646,652],"content":"Syntax","linkify":"Syntax","nodes":[{"content":"Syntax","pos":[0,6]}]},{"pos":[843,853],"content":"Parameters","linkify":"Parameters","nodes":[{"content":"Parameters","pos":[0,10]}]},{"content":"[in] The ID of the thread for which to set the context.","pos":[871,926]},{"content":"[in] The size of the <ph id=\"ph1\">`context`</ph> array.","pos":[950,987],"source":"[in] The size of the `context` array."},{"content":"[in] An array of bytes that describe the thread's context.","pos":[1007,1065]},{"content":"The context specifies the a